The modern equivalent of a battleship is an arsenal ship.

I've got a design of one somewhere but CBA'd to find it while I'm on my phone. Arsenal ships aren't actually a bad idea though, the only reason why the US didn't get them is that the Admiral in charge of the program killed himself and then the Cold War ended, eliminating the need. The concept was based on a study by RAND that determined that if 20% of an invasion force's vehicles were destroyed, the invasion would be unable to continue. To accomplish this, the Navy considered making what was essentially a flat-top VLS farm that could launch hundreds or possibly over a thousand cruise missiles without reloading.
